gomodel:SYNGO_5311  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"Figure 2A shows that, in rat forebrain lysates, endogenous RNF138 was coimmunoprecipitated with CaV2.1, consistent with the idea that the two molecules coexist in the same protein complex in native neurons.\"\n\n\"As depicted in Figure 2B, both RNF138 and CaV2.1 are highly enriched in the SPM fraction, as well as in the SPM subfractions PSD I and PSD II, implying a colocalization of the two proteins at presynaptic and postsynaptic compartments.\"\n\n\"Compared with CaV2.1, RNF138 displays a diffuse immunofluorescence pattern in both axonal and dendrosomatic regions (Fig. 2E, right). Nevertheless, like CaV2.1, RNF138 also shows prominent patterns of punctate staining at presynaptic and postsynaptic sites. Furthermore, CaV2.1 and RNF138 display quantitatively comparable colocalization with the synaptic proteins synaptophysin and PSD-95 (Fig. 2F).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Forebrains from adult Sprague Dawley rats (RRID:RGD_5508397) were homogenized ...\"\n\nantibody:\nrabbit anti-RNF138 (1:200; Abcam catalog #ab92730, RRID:AB_2238719)\n\nconstructs:\n\"cDNAs for human RNF128 and RNF138, as well as rat RNF138, were subcloned into the pcDNA3-Myc vector (Invitrogen).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5311" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

